    "policy_passages": [
      {
        "id": "PS-001",
        "text": "As an airline agent, you can help users **book**, **modify**, or **cancel** flight reservations.",
        "section": "Airline Agent Policy"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-002",
        "text": "You also handle **refunds and compensation**.",
        "section": "Airline Agent Policy"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-003",
        "text": "Before taking any actions that update the booking database (booking, modifying flights, editing baggage, changing cabin class, or updating passenger information), you must list the action details and obtain explicit user confirmation (yes) to proceed.",
        "section": "Airline Agent Policy"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-055",
        "text": "First, the agent must obtain the user id and reservation id.",
        "section": "Cancel flight"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-056",
        "text": "The user must provide their user id.",
        "section": "Cancel flight"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-057",
        "text": "If the user doesn't know their reservation id, the agent should help locate it using available tools.",
        "section": "Cancel flight"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-058",
        "text": "The agent must also obtain the reason for cancellation (change of plan, airline cancelled flight, or other reasons)",
        "section": "Cancel flight"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-059",
        "text": "If any portion of the flight has already been flown, the agent cannot help and transfer is needed.",
        "section": "Cancel flight"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-060",
        "text": "Otherwise, flight can be cancelled if any of the following is true:\n- The booking was made within the last 24 hrs\n- The flight is cancelled by airline\n- It is a business flight\n- The user has travel insurance and the reason for cancellation is covered by insurance.",
        "section": "Cancel flight"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-061",
        "text": "The API does not check that cancellation rules are met, so the agent must make sure the rules apply before calling the API!",
        "section": "Cancel flight"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-062",
        "text": "The refund will go to original payment methods within 5 to 7 business days.",
        "section": "Cancel flight"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-063",
        "text": "Do not proactively offer a compensation unless the user explicitly asks for one.",
        "section": "Refunds and Compensation"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-064",
        "text": "Do not compensate if the user is regular member and has no travel insurance and flies (basic) economy.",
        "section": "Refunds and Compensation"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-065",
        "text": "Always confirms the facts before offering compensation.",
        "section": "Refunds and Compensation"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-066",
        "text": "Only compensate if the user is a silver/gold member or has travel insurance or flies business.",
        "section": "Refunds and Compensation"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-067",
        "text": "If the user complains about cancelled flights in a reservation, the agent can offer a certificate as a gesture after confirming the facts, with the amount being $100 times the number of passengers.",
        "section": "Refunds and Compensation"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-068",
        "text": "If the user complains about delayed flights in a reservation and wants to change or cancel the reservation, the agent can offer a certificate as a gesture after confirming the facts and changing or cancelling the reservation, with the amount being $50 times the number of passengers.",
        "section": "Refunds and Compensation"
      },
      {
        "id": "PS-069",
        "text": "Do not offer compensation for any other reason than the ones listed above.",
        "section": "Refunds and Compensation"
      }
    ],
